Flexible working arrangements – We support customers globally and understand life doesn’t fit neatly into a 9am - 5pm role. We offer flexibility to help you perform at your best.

Company Description


Nearmap is the Australian-founded, global tech pioneer innovating the location intelligence game. Customers rely on Nearmap for consistent, reliable, high-resolution imagery, insights, and answers to create meaningful change in the world and propel industries forward.

Harnessing its own patented camera systems, imagery capture, AI, geospatial tools, and advanced SaaS platforms, Nearmap stands as the definitive source of truth that shapes the livable world.

Job Description


Nearmap's Data Science team designs, prototypes, and develops machine learning products using Nearmap imagery data. As a Senior Data Scientist (Model R&D), you will own the statistical and practical performance of models that ship – framing problems, selecting modelling approaches, training and validating models, identifying failure modes, and improving results through modelling choices, data strategy, and disciplined evaluation. Off-the-shelf models, with minor fine tuning often do not suit our needs, so expect to be making complex decisions about problem formation/specification and model architecture. You will work closely with Machine Learning Engineers who build the training and deployment infrastructure. Your core accountability is the quality, robustness, and suitability of the predictions those tools produce.

Important: This is a hands-on modelling role focused on novel approaches to computer vision and deep learning. If your strength is dashboards, BI, reporting, classical modelling, or deployment of off-the-shelf models, this role is not the right fit for you.

What You’ll Do

Own the modelling lifecycle end-to-end: problem formulation → dataset strategy → training → evaluation → error analysis → improvement

Develop, or select and make novel adaptations to, model architectures for 2D/3D vision tasks using Nearmap’s multi-date, multi-angle, and 3D data
Use PyTorch and important associated packages and libraries (timm, xformers) to develop bespoke models that underlie Nearmap products.
Remain familiar with core conceptual elements of modern deep learning (attention, positional encoding, receptive field, pre-training), so that you can develop and adapt models to fit our needs.
Keep up to date with important developments in the field, such as innovations in the fields of vision and 3D
Design experiments and ablations to understand what drives performance and to de-risk model changes
Improve model performance through sampling strategies, labelling guidance, quality checks, and targeted collection for hard/rare cases
Work with ML Engineers to productionise models and ensure they are robust (monitoring, regression testing, reproducibility)
Communicate clearly about trade-offs, failure modes, and performance, primarily to technical stakeholders

Qualifications


Required

Background in a relevant discipline (Computer Science, Mathematics, Physics, or similar)
Strong grasp of core ML fundamentals and the ability to explain them clearly (validation, regularisation, optimisation, over/underfitting, error analysis)
Hands-on experience training and evaluating ML models end-to-end, including designing baselines and iterating based on evidence
Strong coding ability in scientific Python in a Linux environment, using Git for source control
Demonstrated scientific rigour: forming hypotheses, designing experiments, and interpreting results using appropriate metrics and statistical reasoning
Experience delivering outcomes in real-world settings (shipping models, improving model quality over time, or delivering robust research prototypes)


Desirable

Computer vision experience (segmentation, detection, representation learning)
Experience working with geospatial data, aerial/satellite imagery, multi-view imagery, or multi-temporal imagery
Experience with 3D vision / photogrammetry / structure-from-motion, or working with point clouds / 3D meshes
Experience improving models via data strategy (label quality, sampling, active learning, hard-negative mining, dataset auditing)
Experience training at scale (GPUs, distributed training) and working with large datasets that require efficient IO and compute
Cloud computing experience (AWS or GCP)
Software engineering skills for contributing production-quality code to shared codebases (testing, reproducibility, documentation)


Personal Attributes

Curiosity and learning mindset: you keep your fundamentals fresh and stay up to date with modern deep learning
Pragmatism: you are capable of novelty and creativity, but not for its own sake: you prioritise solutions that work and ship over novelty
Strong judgment and “model taste”: you can choose sensible baselines, interpret failures, and iterate effectively
Collaboration: you communicate well, share knowledge, and work effectively in teams

Additional Information


Some of our benefits

Nearmap takes a holistic approach to our employees’ emotional, physical and financial wellness. Some of our current benefits include:

Quarterly wellbeing day off - Four additional days off annually for your 'YOU' Days
Wellbeing and technology allowance
Annual flu vaccinations
Hybrid flexibility for this role 
Nearmap subscription (of course!)
Work from Anywhere policy for up to 4 weeks each year
Stocked kitchen with access to all the snacks you need
In-office catered lunch every Tuesday and Thursday at our Sydney CBD office
Showers available for anyone cycling to work or lunchtime gym-goers!

Working at Nearmap
We move fast and work smart; often wearing multiple hats. We adapted to remote working with ease and are continually looking at ways to improve. We’re proud of our inclusive, supportive culture, and maintain a safe environment where everyone feels a sense of belonging and can be themselves.

At Nearmap, we embrace a flexible hybrid approach that empowers teams to determine what works best for them. Rather than mandating specific office days, we trust our teams to collaborate with their managers and decide when in-person time adds the most value.

This means you'll have the flexibility to balance remote work with office collaboration in a way that suits your role, your team, and your life. There are no company-wide mandatory office days, giving you the autonomy to work where you're most productive while staying connected with your colleagues.
If you can see yourself working at Nearmap and feel you have the right level of experience, we invite you to get in touch. 

Nearmap AI

Why Join Us?

Work with the Best – Collaborate with some of the brightest minds in fintech, financial services, and strategy.

As a Lead Data Scientist, you'll lead a growing data science team and play a pivotal role in shaping and delivering data-driven solutions across stakeholders. Your primary responsibilities include leading and mentoring your team, designing and implementing advanced machine learning and statistical models, translating complex business problems into scalable data products, and leading the end-to-end lifecycle from discovery to production. You will lead by example with modern data science techniques and tooling, providing clear technical direction and coaching to team members. 

We’re looking for a collaborative team player who thrives in a dynamic environment, embraces the challenge of legacy systems, remains composed under pressure, and is driven to deliver continuous improvement and strategic impact.  This role provides a unique opportunity to connect directly with our stakeholders.  You should be a versatile data leader who can both drive hands-on delivery and lead the development of new data initiatives—balancing strategic oversight with practical execution. 

 

 

Job Description

On a typical day you will: 

Lead, mentor and motivate a data science team (up to10 people) and set the technical direction and standards 
Collaborate within a cross-functional digital team, including Product Management, Engineering and Design. 
Bridge the gap between business problems and data science solutions, turning opportunities into impactful, production-ready models. 
Utilise strong analytical and modelling skills to design, build, and validate machine learning solutions, particularly tree-based methods (e.g. XGBoost, GBM, LightGBM), neural networks, and transformer-based approaches. 
Define and lead the end-to-end lifecycle of data products in an agile environment, from problem framing and experimentation through to deployment and monitoring. 
Conduct and document detailed analysis, including business case development, to prioritise use cases and clearly communicate trade-offs and expected value to stakeholders. 
Work closely with data and platform engineers on ETL pipelines, containerised solutions (e.g. Docker, Kubernetes), and cloud-based environments (e.g. GCP, AWS, Azure), with exposure to modern data platforms such as Snowflake and Databricks. 
Collaborate with cross-functional Agile teams (Engineering, Product, Design, QA) in remote and on-site settings, applying appropriate governance and engagement models to data projects. 
Provide BAU support for existing models and data products, while actively managing demand, prioritisation, and stakeholder expectations to create space for strategic, high-impact data science initiatives. 
Qualifications
Proven end-to-end Data Science experience (6+ years), including recent experience operating at Senior/Lead level 
Proven ability to lead, mentor and motivate a data science team (typically 3–10 people) and to set technical direction and standards 
Strong, hands-on expertise with modern machine learning models and algorithms, particularly tree-based methods (e.g. XGBoost, GBM, LightGBM), statistical models, and neural networks 
Demonstrated experience working with LLMs, transformers and embeddings in practical, production-oriented use cases 
Solid understanding of the end-to-end lifecycle of data products, from problem framing and model development through to productisation, pipelining and BAU support 
Proficiency in Python and a strong command of SQL for data exploration, feature engineering and model implementation 
Experience working with cloud platforms (e.g. GCP, AWS or Azure) and familiarity with modern data ecosystems such as Snowflake and/or Databricks (or ability to upskill quickly) 
Exposure to containerised solutions (e.g. Docker) and collaborating with engineers on production deployment and MLOps practices 
Strong stakeholder management and communication skills, with the ability to translate business problems into data solutions and tell a compelling story with insights 
Experience contributing to or leading governance and engagement models (e.g. steering committees, RACI/RASCI frameworks, working groups) across multiple stakeholders 
Demonstrated capability in prioritisation and managing tradeoffs in a resourceconstrained or scaleup environment, including pushing back on lowvalue work 
Experience developing or contributing to business cases for data and AI initiatives, including articulating value, risks and assumptions 
Additional Information

Who are we?

At Liontown Resources, our Kathleen Valley operation is moving confidently into full-scale production. Following our recent capital raise and significant investment in growth, we're expanding our technical teams to support the long-term success of the mine.

We're now seeking a Control Systems Engineer to join our process plant maintenance and planning team, ensuring our plant control systems are optimised, reliable, and ready to meet the demands of production.

Why join now?

With our production ramp-up in full swing, this is a pivotal time to be part of Liontown. Our focus is on building a safe, reliable, and efficient operation - and this role will directly influence the performance and sustainability of our processing operations.

What you'll be doing

Reporting to the Control Systems and Technology Superintendent, you will:

Provide technical support for the operation, maintenance, and optimisation of plant control systems.

Implement control strategies and system changes on an operating plant safely and efficiently.

Monitor, troubleshoot, and maintain operational technology (OT), PLC, SCADA, and DCS systems.

Conduct system backups, availability and redundancy checks to maintain operational integrity.

Support continuous improvement initiatives, alarm rationalisation, and alarm management.

Partner with the maintenance, operations, and reliability teams to enhance plant stability and performance.

What you will bring

Experience with Citect SCADA, Allen-Bradley PLCs, and HMI programming.

Strong understanding of Operational Technology (OT) systems and virtualization environments.

Experience with Active Directory management and server/PC administration.

Skilled in industrial networking, including Cisco and Allen-Bradley Stratix switches, subnetting, VLAN configuration, and communication protocols such as Modbus TCP and Ethernet/IP.

Familiarity with telemetry systems for remote monitoring and control.

Knowledge of instrumentation, including 4-20 mA loops and scaling principles.

Experience tuning and optimising PID control loops within process control systems.

Exposure to OSIsoft PI systems (PI-AF, PI Vision, SMT) highly desirable.

What we're looking for

We're looking for someone who brings:

Degree qualifications in Electrical, Control Systems, Mechatronics, or related engineering discipline.

Experience as a Control Systems Engineer (or similar) in mining or heavy industry processing.

Knowledge of PLC, SCADA, and DCS systems, with strong problem-solving skills.

Exposure to process plant maintenance planning and reliability strategies.

Strong communication, organisational, and teamwork skills.

Self-motivation and the ability to work independently with initiative.

Ability to meet site requirements, including a current National Police Clearance (or ability to obtain), pre-employment medical, and drug & alcohol screen.

Why Liontown

At Liontown, you'll be joining a company that's helping drive the clean energy future. Our operations are designed with sustainability at their core — powered by renewables and built for long-term impact.

This is your opportunity to take ownership of a pivotal technical role during a major project phase, while enjoying the stability of a long-term site-based position.

Visit: liontown.com to learn more.

AIR6500 will provide a Joint Air Battle Management System capability for the Royal Australian Air Force. The system will provide multi-domain integration of air, electromagnetic, and missile defence battle management including deployable & fixed operations centres, communications, and both active & passive sensors. The AIR6500 Hardware Engineering Lead as a member in the System Engineering Integration Team (SEIT) has the responsibility for providing technical guidance and ensuring design integrity and consistency of the Hardware components across the program throughout the project lifecycle. Your primary responsibility is to oversee and lead the Hardware technical aspects of the project, ensuring that all design and development activities are completed to the highest standard and meet the required technical specifications.

Responsibilities

Working on the AIR6500 project the Hardware Engineering Lead will provide services including but not limited to:

·         Provide oversight to all IPTs for Hardware development across the program

·         Drive the AIR6500 Hardware solution and interfaces in the architectural model to the AIR6500 solution

·         Review and guidance of Hardware and non-functional related requirements, product trades, and the sell-off approach

·         Work with IPTs and System Architects to establish hardware requirements and sizing for AIR6500 elements

·         Work with the SEIT Lead to drive the development of key AIR6500 technical documents and artefacts such as solution description, trade studies, and definition of requirements

·         Capture and assess Hardware metrics (e.g., on-time releases, quality / defect, supplier impact)

·         Work with a broad set of stakeholders across the Lockheed Martin Business and design partners for the achievement of common goals

·         Provide oversight and validation of subcontractor analysis reports

·         Provide cross skilling and knowledge transfer to LMA engineers

·         Desire to 'roll up the sleeves' and execute activities in addition to providing review and mentoring roles.

·         Drive development of AIR6500 deployable elements and ruggedized solutions for packaging hardware components.

·         Author technical documentation and develop Technical Data packs as required

·         Develop Test Plans, Procedures and Test reports as required

·         Perform Trade Studies to evaluate possible technical substitutions as required

 

About you:

About the program:

LMA has entered into an arrangement with BAE, Saab and CoA (MIWS) for the execution of all Combat System Integration work related to the Aegis Surface Combatant fleet. 

The agreement, called the Combat Systems Integration – Integrated Project Team (CSI-IPT) Collaboration Agreement or CCA forms a collaborative enterprise organisation to execute scopes of work across Hobart Class Destroyer (SEA4000 Phase 6 and other related Destroyer Capability Enhancement (DCE) upgrades) and the Hunter Class Frigates (HCFs - SEA5000 Phase 1). The CSI-IPT evolves the current independently executing programs such as SEA4000 Phase  6 and SEA5000 Phase 1 under an umbrella enterprise organisation formed as a program of programs.

About Toshiba

Established in Australia in 1978, Toshiba International Corporation Pty Ltd (TIC) is a wholly owned subsidiary of Toshiba Corporation, Japan. TIC has established itself as a market leader in the power generation sector in Australia, providing industrial equipment, generators, turbines, transformers, motors, battery energy storage equipment and associated power infrastructure for this industry, including both the supply and installation of new equipment and the maintenance or upgrading of existing equipment. Our Company consists of engineering, technical, commercial and business development staff, with all staff focusing on customer needs (mostly the owners/operators and developers of power stations including thermal, hydro-electric, wind and battery energy storage and transmission and distribution plant).

Job Summary

With the recent growth in Digital Asset Management capability and workload, TIC is seeking a highly motivated Asset Management and Analytics Professional to join the ESS business.  The role is focused on working with our customers during the implementation and operation of our Asset Performance and Condition Monitoring Platform (Digital Twin), based on the EtaPRO® platform (https://etapro.com/).  As such, the role requires a working knowledge of power generation facilities, including steam turbine generator-based systems.  It is anticipated that the ideal candidate will bring process mechanical capability, broad thermodynamic knowledge and experience to this role.

Key Responsibilities:

Apply mechanical / process engineering knowledge across the ESS Asset Performance and Condition Monitoring business operations, including:

Working with the existing team to support the safe implementation and operation of online Digital Twin platforms for Toshiba Power Generation customers in Australia, New Zealand, Southeast Asia and other global regions

Providing engineering support to operations and maintenance activities / sustaining capital projects identified through the operation of the EtaPRO platform

Providing process / mechanical technical support to broader ESS business activities from time to time (for example capital project development activity associated with the deployment of Toshiba energy systems)

Work closely with Toshiba teams globally to understand Toshiba ESS Asset Performance and Condition Monitoring technology in order to effectively develop and deploy the technology across TIC regions of responsibility

Our ideal candidate will possess:

Relevant work experience in the power generation sector, including experience in steam turbine generator or boiler-based systems

Tertiary qualifications in Process, Mechanical or a relevant and related field of Engineering

Technical understanding of power generation facilities, including working at power station sites in operations, reliability or process engineering roles

Technical understanding of thermodynamic modelling

Project management experience (preferable)

Ability to work on-site and away from home when required

An Australian Driver’s License (essential)
